    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Blog-to-X Thread Converter\\n\",\"**NLP Project 48 of 100** — Convert a blog article into a short social media thread.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import re, requests\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"BLOG = \\\"\\\"\\\"Why Every Developer Should Learn SQL\\n\\nSQL isn't just for data analysts. Every developer interacts with databases. Understanding SQL makes you faster at debugging, better at architecture decisions, and more effective in code reviews. The basics take a weekend to learn but pay dividends for your entire career. Start with SELECT, JOIN, and GROUP BY. Then learn indexing, query optimization, and window functions.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\ndef blog_to_thread(text, max_tweets=6):\\n    sentences = re.split(r'(?<=[.!?])\\\\s+', text.strip())\\n    tweets = []\\n    current = ''\\n    for sent in sentences:\\n        if len(current) + len(sent) < 260:\\n            current += ' ' + sent if current else sent\\n        else:\\n            if current: tweets.append(current.strip())\\n            current = sent\\n    if current: tweets.append(current.strip())\\n    \\n    thread = []\\n    for i, tweet in enumerate(tweets[:max_tweets]):\\n        prefix = '🧵' if i == 0 else f'{i}.'\\n        thread.append(f'{prefix} {tweet}')\\n    thread.append(f'\\\\n{len(thread)+1}. If you found this useful, repost ♻️ and follow for more!')\\n    return thread\\n\\nthread = blog_to_thread(BLOG)\\nfor t in thread:\\n    print(t)\\n    print()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Thread conversion breaks long content** into tweet-sized chunks.\\n\",\"- **Preserves logical flow** while respecting character limits.\\n\",\"- **For production, use LLMs** for more creative thread formatting.\"]}\n",
